  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.20259146
    description: "Version DOI for v0.1.7."
abstract: >
  QMaxent integrates the elapid Python library into QGIS to provide
  Maxent-style species distribution modeling (SDM) without leaving the
  GIS desktop. It supports model training, spatial projection, spatial
  cross-validation (Geographic K-Fold as the default; Checkerboard,
  Random K-Fold, Buffered Leave-One-Out), jackknife and permutation
  variable importance, export of QGIS-resident data to maxent.jar-
  compatible formats (SWD or ESRI ASCII Grid), and stratified priority-
  site selection for post-prediction field surveys — all in one GIS
  session. Dependencies are isolated in a plugin-private virtual
  environment that does not affect the host QGIS Python installation.
# Note: a `preferred-citation:` block pointing at the accompanying
# manuscript will be added here once that manuscript is accepted for
# publication. Until then this file cites the software only, which is
# the canonical record for users who need to cite QMaxent right now.
